South Korea is taking a bold step by bringing AI directly into the classroom. Starting in March 2025, schools will begin using AI-powered digital textbooks for subjects like math, English, and computer science. These smart tools adapt to student needs and support teachers, not replace them. This article explains what South Korea is doing, how it works, and what other countries can learn from it.Best online courses https://www.blockchain-council.org/certifications/certified-bitcoin-expert-cbie/
